<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> <h1><a name="Documentation_Best_Practices_Add"></a>  Documentation Best Practices: Adding Warnings and Notes </h1>
<p />
<form name="EDITTHIS" action="/bin/edit/Documentation/DocBestPracticesWarningsAndNotes" method="get"><input type="submit" value="Edit section" alt="Edit this section" title="Click to edit this section" class="twikiButton" style="font-size:0.75em;"><input type="hidden" value="1487216515" name="t"></form>
<p />
This describes how to put in a Note, Warning or Important comment that is set off from the regular text. The variables described below are defined in <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/WebPreferences" class="twikiLink">WebPreferences</a> (soon in <a href="/bin/view/Main/TWikiPreferences" class="twikiLink">TWikiPreferences</a>).
<p />
<h3><a name="Notes"></a> Notes </h3>
Notes are asides about the contents of the text that provide specific information that particular, but not all, users may need. Notes are less necessary than <strong>Importants</strong> and unlike <strong>Warnings</strong>, may not cause harm if ignored.
<p />
<h4><a name="Usage"></a> Usage </h4>
To create a note, insert the <code>%NOTE%</code> variable, followed by a single space and your text:
<pre>
&#37;NOTE&#37; Here is my note text.
</pre>
<p />
<h4><a name="Example"></a> Example </h4>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> NOTE </font></strong> </dt><dd>  Something that I want you to know about and pay some attention to.
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<!-- <code><b>====BEGIN THE SECTION FOR INCLUDING ====</b></code>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> NOTE </font></strong> </dt><dd> 
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<code><b>==</b></code> END SECTION <code><b>==</b></code> -->
<p />
<p />
<h3><a name="Importants"></a> Importants </h3>
<strong>Importants</strong> are asides from your normal text that you want to highlight so that skimming users will not ignore them. Unlike warnings, they will not cause grave harm to the system or person if ignored. The difference between a <strong>Note</strong> and an <strong>Important</strong> is up to the writer.
<p />
<h4><a name="Usage_AN1"></a> Usage </h4>
Importants are included by putting, on a new line, <code>%IMPORTANT%</code> followed by a single space and your important text:
<pre>
&#37;IMPORTANT&#37; Some text about the important thing.
</pre>
<p />
<h4><a name="Example_AN1"></a> Example </h4>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/warning.gif" alt="ALERT!" title="ALERT!" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#008000"> IMPORTANT </font></strong> </dt><dd>  Don't forget to include a single space or the <strong>Important</strong> will not work.
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<!-- <code><b>==</b></code> BEGIN INCLUDE SECTION <code><b>==</b></code>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/warning.gif" alt="ALERT!" title="ALERT!" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#008000"> IMPORTANT </font></strong> </dt><dd> 
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<code><b>==</b></code> END SECTION <code><b>==</b></code> -->
<p />
<p />
<h3><a name="Disclaimers"></a> Disclaimers </h3>
<strong>Disclaimers</strong> are asides from your normal text that you want to highlight so that users will not ignore them. Normally they limit the context of the document, its applicability. Unlike warnings, they will not cause grave harm to the system or person if ignored. The difference between a <strong>Note</strong> and an <strong>Important</strong> and a <strong>Disclaimer</strong> is up to the writer.
<p />
<h4><a name="Usage_AN2"></a> Usage </h4>
Disclaimers are included by putting, on a new line, <code>%DISCLAIMER%</code> followed by a single space and your disclaimer text:
<pre>
&#37;DISCLAIMER&#37; The content of the disclaimer.
</pre>
<p />
<h4><a name="Example_AN2"></a> Example </h4>
%DISCLAIMER% This applies only to documents in this twiki.
<p />
<!-- <code><b>==</b></code> BEGIN INCLUDE SECTION <code><b>==</b></code>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> DISCLAIMER </font></strong> </dt><dd> 
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<code><b>==</b></code> END SECTION <code><b>==</b></code> -->
<p />
<p />
<h3><a name="Warnings"></a> Warnings </h3>
<strong>Warnings</strong> are set off from the regular flow of the text to especially warn the reader about an action that could cause harm to the system or to the user. It's less than something that should be labeled <strong>DANGER</strong> but more harmful than something that you would put into an <strong>Important</strong>. 
<p />
If something that you are instructing a user to do could take up the CPU for several minutes, you should put in a <strong>Warning</strong>.
<p />
<h4><a name="Usage_AN3"></a> Usage </h4>
Warnings are added by putting, on a new line, <code>%WARNING%</code> followed by a single space and your text.
<pre>
&#37;WARNING&#37; Some text here.
</pre>
<p />
<h4><a name="Example_AN3"></a> Example </h4>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/warning.gif" alt="ALERT!" title="ALERT!" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> WARNING! </font></strong> </dt><dd>  If ignore me, you'll regret it.
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<!-- <code><b>==</b></code> BEGIN INCLUDE SECTION <code><b>==</b></code>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/warning.gif" alt="ALERT!" title="ALERT!" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> WARNING! </font></strong> </dt><dd> 
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<code><b>==</b></code> END SECTION <code><b>==</b></code> -->
<p />
<p />
<h3><a name="Tips"></a> Tips </h3>
(I'm not sure I like tips as being separate from Notes, but they're in the text in places, so here's a solution.)
<p />
<h4><a name="Usage_AN4"></a> Usage </h4>
Tips are added by putting, on a new line, <code>%TIP%</code> followed by a single space and your text.
<pre>
&#37;TIP&#37; Some text here.
</pre>
<p />
<h4><a name="Example_AN4"></a> Example </h4>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#008000"> TIP </font></strong> </dt><dd>  If ignore me, you'll regret it.
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<!-- <code><b>==</b></code> BEGIN INCLUDE SECTION <code><b>==</b></code>
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#008000"> TIP </font></strong> </dt><dd> 
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<code><b>==</b></code> END SECTION <code><b>==</b></code> -->
<p />
<h4><a name="OSG_1_2_Tag"></a> OSG 1.2 Tag </h4>
<strong>OSG</strong> is used to set off items in the release documentation that apply to the OSG 1.2 release.
<p />
<h4><a name="Example_AN5"></a> Example </h4>
<p />
%OSG12% This item apples to OSG 1.2. %ENDOSG12%
<p />
<!-- <code><b>====BEGIN THE SECTION FOR INCLUDING ====</b></code>
<p />
   <div style="border:1px solid rgb(153, 153, 153); background-color: rgb(255,247,202);"> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> For OSG 1.2 </font></strong> <br/>
<p />
<code><b>==</b></code> END SECTION <code><b>==</b></code> -->
<p />
<!-- <code><b>====BEGIN THE SECTION FOR INCLUDING ====</b></code>
<p />
   </div>  
<p />
<code><b>==</b></code> END SECTION <code><b>==</b></code> -->
